&gt;&gt; Ah, a subject I can comment on with authority... killing ants and things
&gt;&gt; that sting is my specialty here in Mexico...you&#39;ll love the simple
&gt;&gt; answer...laundry detergent. I can tell you stories of tiny crazy ants to
&gt;&gt; ants as large as half your thumb...tried all kinds of things like
&gt;&gt; chlorine...acid...but a hand full of cheap, cheap, blue laundry
&gt;&gt; detergent mixed in water will kill ants on the spot...dead, done, gone,
&gt;&gt; ready for an EVP session. What a blessing since I am highly allergic to
&gt;&gt; all pesticides. Getting ants out of an electrical system is another
&gt;&gt; matter. I have them running along by house electrical lines and must
&gt;&gt; wait for them to show their face before I soap em. Ron L
